## Constructors to the Rescue!

A **Constructor** is a special "setup" function inside the class that runs EXACTLY ONCE the instant an object is created.

It shares the EXACT same name as the class.

```dart
class Player {
  String name;

  // This is the Constructor! It acts like a parameter funnel.
  Player(String startingName) {
    name = startingName;
  }
}
```

## Required Data

Now, because we added parameters to `Player()`, Dart will REFUSE to build the object unless you pass the required data in immediately.

```dart
void main() {
  // Player p1 = Player(); <-- ERROR! Missing the starting name!

  Player p1 = Player('Mario'); // Works perfectly!
  Player p2 = Player('Luigi'); // Works perfectly!
}
```

