## Super-fast Constructors

Typing `name = startingName;` is annoying.
Dart has an ultimate shortcut using the `this` keyword to directly funnel the parameter into the property automatically.

```dart
class Player {
  String name;
  int health;

  // Instant setup in one line!
  Player(this.name, this.health);
}
```
It's magical. You'll use this format 99% of the time in Dart and Flutter.
